AGI - The Russian Investigative Committee has established that the authors of the terrorist attack at Crocus City Hall, which last March 22 cost their lives to at least 143 people, were heading to Kiev after the attack. The press service of the Russian investigative committee reported it to TASS. All their actions were supervised by a man through Telegram. "According to the instructions of the coordinator, the terrorists, after committing the crime, drove to the Russian-Ukrainian border and then crossed it and arrived in Kiev to receive the promised reward," reads in the message. The defendants affirmed in their initial testimony that "their actions, both in the preparation phase and after the armed attack on Crocus City Hall, were coordinated by voice messages through the Telegram messenger by a man who presented themselves under a pseudonym". Previously, the investigative committee of the Russian Federation reported that investigators had received information on providing terrorists with large sums of money and cryptocurrencies from Ukraine and that they had used these funds to prepare the terrorist attack. According to the Department, the first results of the investigations have fully confirmed the planned nature of criminal actions, as well as the careful preparation and financial support from the crime organizers.
